# Implementation Plan — Deferred Donation Updates

## Goal Description
The user wants to improve the UX for updating recurring donations. Currently, the update happens immediately (and overwrites an existing receipt). The new requirement is to reflect that the update takes effect **next month** (on the next billing cycle).
The changes include updating the UI to show `[old] --> [new]` amounts, adding a "next month" placeholder receipt in the donation history, sending an immediate "Amount Changed" email, and reverting the backend so that we don't destructively overwrite old receipts.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Reverting Backend Overwrite**: As discussed, I will revert the backend logic so that when a billing rollover happens, a **new** receipt is generated rather than overwriting the previous month's receipt. This ensures accurate history.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Email Notifications**: I will implement the two-step email flow:
> 1. An immediate "Your monthly donation amount has changed" email when you click update.
> 2. The standard "Thank you for your donation" receipt email when the actual payment processes.

