## Proposed Changes

### Backend Updates

#### [MODIFY] [server/src/routes/subscriptions.js](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/OneDrive/Documents/Donation%20site/Donation-Site-Project/server/src/routes/subscriptions.js)
- **Immediate Email**: In `POST /update`, before the mock timeout, immediately dispatch an email to the user stating "Your scheduled monthly donation amount has been updated to $[amount]."
- **Revert Receipt Overwrite**: In the mock rollover timeout, remove the `tx.transaction.update` logic. Return it to `tx.transaction.create` so that a new transaction row is properly created for the new billing cycle.
- **Provide Scheduled Amount**: In `GET /user/dashboard`, return `scheduledAmount` to the frontend by checking the `global.scheduledSubscriptionUpdates` map. (Or, pass it alongside `monthlyAmount`).

### Frontend UI

#### [MODIFY] [client/src/pages/DashboardPage.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/OneDrive/Documents/Donation%20site/Donation-Site-Project/client/src/pages/DashboardPage.jsx)
- **State**: Ensure `scheduledAmount` is fetched and tracked in the state from the dashboard API response.
- **Pass Props**: Pass `scheduledAmount` to `UserSummaryCard`.
- **Donation History Timeline**: In the history list, if a `scheduledAmount` exists, manually inject a placeholder "Upcoming" transaction at the top of the timeline array before mapping over it.
  - This placeholder will use a distinct visual style (e.g., a "special up arrow" icon `↑`, grayed out or dashed border).
  - It will **not** be clickable (no receipt modal).
  - It will say "Scheduled for Next Month".

#### [MODIFY] [client/src/components/dashboard/UserSummaryCard.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/OneDrive/Documents/Donation%20site/Donation-Site-Project/client/src/components/dashboard/UserSummaryCard.jsx)
- **Props**: Accept `scheduledAmount`.
- **Stats Display**: In the "Monthly" stat block, check if `scheduledAmount` exists and is different from `monthlyAmount`.
- If true, render the text as: `$X/mo --> $Y/mo`.
- Add a subtle Framer Motion animation or color highlight (using the OpenmindProjects brand guide) to the `--> $Y/mo` to draw attention to the pending upgrade/downgrade.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- None required for this UI change.

### Manual Verification
1. Log into the dashboard.
2. Click to update the donation amount to a new value and confirm.
3. Observe the "Monthly" stat change from `$old --> $new`.
4. Observe the top of the Donation History timeline showing an unclickable entry with an up arrow for the upcoming amount.
5. Check backend logs to verify the "Amount Changed" email was dispatched immediately.
6. Wait 5 seconds for the mock rollover, observe that the `scheduledAmount` state clears, the stats show `$new/mo` only, and the timeline shows a real, clickable receipt for the new amount.
7. Check backend logs to verify the "Receipt" email was dispatched during rollover.
